@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam defaultFontName Inter
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #333333
  LifeLineBorderColor #1A73E8
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #E8F0FE
}
skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #F3E8FD
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF3E0
  BorderColor #E65100
}

title Voxelize Navmesh — Data Flow Sequence

participant "LiDAR\n(30 Hz)" as LiDAR
participant "Voxelizer Node\n(C++, PCL)" as Vox
participant "Static Map\n(unordered_set)" as Map
participant "Obstacle Manager\n(Python)" as OM
participant "Tile Cache\n(Detour)" as TC
participant "Crowd\n(Detour)" as Crowd
participant "Robot\n(cmd_vel)" as Robot

== LiDAR Processing (C++) ==

LiDAR -> Vox : sensor_msgs::PointCloud2
Vox -> Vox : 1. Range filter (sensor frame)
Vox -> Vox : 2. Transform to map frame
Vox -> Vox : 3. pcl::VoxelGrid downsample
Vox -> Vox : 4. Snap to voxel centres

loop for each voxel
  Vox -> Map : Chebyshev neighbourhood probe
  Map --> Vox : hit? → static \nmiss? → foreground
end

Vox -> OM : /foreground_cloud (PointCloud2)
Vox -> Vox : /full_cloud (PointCloud2)

== Obstacle Clustering (Python) ==

OM -> OM : Voxelise to 3D occupancy grid
OM -> OM : 6-adjacency BFS flood fill
OM -> OM : Connected components → cylinder fit
OM -> OM : Diff against previous frame

== Dynamic Obstacle Handling ==

alt Crowd-agent pool mode
  OM -> Crowd : Add zero-velocity agents
  Crowd -> Crowd : dtCrowd::update()
  note right: Fast, simple. Scales poorly\nabove ~100 agents.
else TileCache cylinder mode
  OM -> TC : dtTileCache::addObstacle(cylinder)
  TC -> TC : Rebuild overlapping tiles (<1ms each)
  TC -> TC : dtNavMesh updated in-place
  note right: More compute per frame.\nScales to thousands of points.
end

== Navigation Output ==

Crowd -> Robot : /cmd_vel (Twist)\nvia Power Cosine Gating
note right of Robot
  Linear velocity scaled by
  |cos(angular_error)|⁴
  Crisp, oscillation-free steering.
end note

@enduml
